Introduced
Second Regular Session 124th General Assembly (2026)
SENATE RESOLUTION ____
MR. PRESIDENT:
I offer the following resolution and move its adoption:
1 A SENATE RESOLUTION congratulating the Cascade
2 High School football team on winning the 2025 Indiana High
3 School Athletic Association (IHSAA) Class 3A state
4 championship title.
5 Whereas, On November 28, 2025, the Cascade High School
6 football team finalized their season at Lucas Oil Stadium in
7 Indianapolis, Indiana, by winning their first football state
8 championship title in school history;
9 Whereas, With a perfect 15-0 season, the Cascade Cadets
10 advanced to the state championship game against Fort Wayne
11 Bishop Luers High School after multiple thrilling match-ups,
12 including a 77-0 blowout against Frankfort and beating Gibson
13 Southern 49-34 at Semi-State by securing two interceptions;
14 Whereas, During the state championship game, the Cadets
15 started strong in the first quarter, with a 6-0 advantage
16 following seven consecutive rushing plays that covered 75 yards
17 in 2 minutes, 19 seconds, 57 of those yards in five plays, and
18 their first pass attempt of the game going for a 9-yard
19 touchdown from senior Brady Trebley to senior Delton Howrey;
2026 RR 3505/DI LW

2
1 Whereas, Cascade ended the first quarter with 173 rushing
2 yards and a 19-0 advantage, then the Cadets kept hold of the
3 lead with a stellar defense and a 21-yard field goal by junior
4 Brogan Trump in the second quarter;
5 Whereas, By starting strong and never letting up, the
6 Cascade Cadets won the state championship game with a final
7 score of 29-14;
8 Whereas, Following the game, quarterback Brady Trebley
9 was awarded the Blake Ress Mental Attitude Award for Class
10 3A; and
11 Whereas, Under the leadership of Head Coach Connor
12 Simmons, the Cadets finished their 2025 season with a final
13 record of 15-0 and their first state football title in school
14 history: Therefore,
15 Be it resolved by the Senate of the
16 General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
17 SECTION 1. That the Indiana Senate congratulates the
18 Cascade High School football team on winning the 2025 IHSAA
19 3A state championship.
20 SECTION 2. The Secretary of the Senate is hereby directed
21 to transmit copies of this Resolution to Head Coach Connor
22 Simmons, Principal Jeffrey Hansel, and Superintendent Brian
23 Tomamichel.
2026 RR 3505/DI LW

